crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a Linux ransomware variant, likely part of the 'V-Society' family. It performs recursive directory traversal (sub_403656), renames files with the extension '.v-society', and encrypts their contents using OpenSSL's libcrypto, which it loads dynamically at runtime (sub_404a76). Key malicious behaviors include: 1) terminating processes that hold file locks using 'kill -9' (sub_405208) to ensure encryption completes, 2) dropping ransom notes named '.README_TO_RESTORE', and 3) utilizing multi-threading (pthreads) for efficient bulk encryption. Concrete IOCs include the extension '.v-society', the ransom note name, and the log file 'work.log'.
